  "body": "Currently in LBaaS in openstack (v1 and v2), it puts the LBaaS port in the default security group only. Most environments have that set not to allow any traffic. There's a bug open to ask for a security group when creating an LB, but it hasn't gone anywhere. This means if you use this plugin with kubernetes, it with create the LB and assign a floating ip, but no one will be able to access it. the best fix is allow the config file to specify a security group id- the plugin would get the port_id of the LB after its created and then use update-port (http://gophercloud.io/docs/networking/#update-port) to add the security group to the port. if no security group was supplied in the config file it would behave as it does now.\n",
